Exception Handling in C++ is a process to handle runtime errors. 
throw âˆ’ A program throws an exception when a problem shows up.
catch âˆ’ A program catches an exception with an exception handler.
try âˆ’ A try block identifies which particular exceptions will be activated. 

Advantages of Exception Handling:
1. Exception handling can control run tune errors. 
2. It can separate the error handling code and normal code 
3. It can avoid abnormal termination of the program.
4. It can produce the normal execution flow for a program. 
